com.nhaarman.listviewanimations.itemmanipulation

Interface OnDismissCallback<T extends ViewGroup>

  • All Known Subinterfaces:
    UndoCallback<T>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    SimpleSwipeUndoAdapter, TimedUndoAdapter

    public interface OnDismissCallback<T extends ViewGroup>
    A callback interface used to inform its client about a successful dismissal of one or more list item positions.

    • Method Summary

      Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      void onDismiss(T listView, int[] reverseSortedPositions)
      Called when the user has indicated they she would like to dismiss one or more list item positions.

    • Method Detail

      • onDismiss

        void onDismiss(T listView,
             int[] reverseSortedPositions)
        Called when the user has indicated they she would like to dismiss one or more list item positions. When this method is called given positions should be removed from the adapter.
        Parameters:
        listView - The originating ListView implementation
        reverseSortedPositions - An array of positions to dismiss, sorted in descending order for convenience.
